MAINTENANCE ENGINEER SAFETY & LOTO MANUAL
Document Ref: TRN-2026-004 | Target Role: Maintenance Engineers

1. LOCKOUT / TAGOUT (LOTO) MANDATORY PROTOCOLS
Prior to servicing high-voltage equipment (e.g., Compressor C-12 90kW motor) or pressure vessels (Reactor R-3):
- Step 1: Isolate primary electrical circuit breaker and valve manifold.
- Step 2: Apply personal safety lock and warning tag with Maintenance Engineer employee ID.
- Step 3: Verify zero-energy state using calibrated multimeter and pressure gauge.
- Step 4: Record LOTO verification step in work order notes before proceeding with maintenance.